subSubSection.paragraph:
Comments
: 

S. sphondylii

is commonly found on cow pastures, where it tends to be more frequent on old dung (
Püchel 1993
; 
Pont &Meier 2002
). Males range in colour from dark brown to bright yellow. This species is characterized by an unusual reproductive behaviour (
Martin &Hosken 2004
). Copulations are short but females remate readily. Laboratory trials demonstrate that frequent copulation has astrong negative effect on male longevity, while females are not affected.
